%20surveillance%20gaps%20in%20the%20region.%20Bart%20Hollants%2C%20an%20official%20from%20NATO's%20Allied%20Command%20Transformation%20Branch%2C%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20tangible%20results%26quot%3B%20of%20NATO's%20efforts%20to%20curb%20security%20threats%20in%20the%20Baltic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demonstration%20involved%20NATO%20maritime%20assets%2C%20including%20from%20the%20Royal%20Danish%20and%20German%20navies%2C%20testing%20how%20drones%20work%20together%20with%20crewed%20vessels.%20The%20testing%20activities%20included%20tactical%20maneuvering%20exercises%20like%20live-fire%20events%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20integrating%20drones%20into%20NATO's%20naval%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20announced%20its%20plans%20to%20establish%20Task%20Force%20X%20and%20employ%20naval%20drones%20in%20late%20January.%20The%20aim%20of%20the%20project%20is%20to%20counter%20and%20deter%20state%20and%20non-state%20actors%20from%20sabotaging%20undersea%20cables%2C%20as%20well%20as%20curb%20potential%20Russian%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETask%20Force%20X%20is%20working%20to%20field%20%26quot%3Ba%20fleet%20of%20maritime%20autonomous%20systems%20to%20provide%20persistent%20surveillance%2C%20detect%20and%20track%20potential%20threats%2C%20and%20enhance%20situational%20awareness%2C%26quot%3B%20NATO%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20approach%20offers%20a%20cost-effective%20and%20rapidly%20deployable%20solution%20to%20counter%20Russian%20aggression.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Models%20of%20drones%20are%20kept%20in%20a%20warehouse%20at%20Naval%20Support%20Activity%20Bahrain.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f99a372417f97b87cd4950%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EModels%20of%20drones%20are%20kept%20in%20a%20warehouse%20at%20Naval%20Support%20Activity%20Bahrain.%3Cp%3EJake%20Epstein%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E